    <item>
      <title>14.19 Health Check</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-19-health-check/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-19-health-check/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2025 02:12:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.19 Health Check&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-18-random-attacker/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;By some stroke of luck, Maomao was at Jinshi’s palace.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, yes, you must not have had dinner yet. I have it prepared.” Suiren started to lay out the meal like she was very much her grandmother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was a generous spread of dishes Maomao wanted to eat immediately, but she had to mind her manners. Not only was she not the head of the house, she was in the presence of an imperial. There was no way she could casually dig in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although she often ate first as the food taster, from what she could tell from the table setting, she was being told to join him in his meal.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi slurped a mouthful of congee. “&amp;#8230;You can eat.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I’ve been waiting!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Having received Jinshi’s approval, Maomao helped herself to some congee. The broth was rich with a chicken flavour and there were floating bits of rice and meat.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi studied Maomao as he took a sip of the aperitif. “How has work been lately?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao swallowed the food in her mouth. “No changes for me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nor for I.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nor for I, huh?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As for Maomao, she meant that there were changes for Yao, En’en, and Yo, but there was no need for her to go out of her way to correct it. He would probably tell her that he didn’t ask about her personally.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi looked like he wanted to say something but didn’t know how to bring it up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You don’t have to force yourself to speak.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao ate in silence as she recalled that she was officially here to give the imperial brother a health check. She chewed and gulped down a juicy soup dumpling, then set down her chopsticks. “Jinshi-sama, you look well.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He would usually look exhausted from overwork, but it didn’t seem to be the case today.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, I did acquire a subordinate whom Maomao hates to decrease my workload,” he replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hahaha, if you mean the man with Hu in his name, how about we stage an accident and dispose of him for the sake of the future?” Maomao hated Hulang.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Stop, stop. As it is, Chue would try to take his life if she has the opportunity to do so.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Go, Chue.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao picked up her chopsticks and went for the pickled vegetables.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Besides, that one is useful for all sorts of intelligence,” Jinshi added.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that sooo? What a pity.” She crunched on some pickles.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You also look well, Maomao.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The most stomachache-inducing work is over.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so? Has there been anything out of the ordinary?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Come to think of it, I did get a letter from an inner palace friend.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Your friend&amp;#8230;that would be, the girl who attended the learning centre?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, you remember her.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Was Xiaolan finding what she learnt at the learning centre helpful in her current day-to-day life?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So she learnt her words well enough that she could send a letter.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. However, I can never send her a reply because she forgets to put in her address.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi rubbed his chin. “Shall I look into it then?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, please leave it.” Maomao drank some tea.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why is that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I will send her a reply. I will have to write, ‘Don’t contact the pleasure district. It’ll give rise to strange rumours,’ and end it there.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Normally people don&amp;#8217;t send letters to a brothel.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wouldn’t it be fine if you prepare a different addressee?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wouldn’t that give Chue-san more work?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was enough that Xiaolan was happy. Getting her involved with Maomao would probably get her monitored. Her letters would be inspected and her replies to Maomao would become bland. For Xiaolan to live in peace, the correct answer was for Maomao to not get into contact with her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had too many things she couldn’t speak about, like the emperor’s surgery and smallpox.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, at the same time, she felt like she was doing Xiaolan a disservice.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao didn’t want to send a reply because she wanted to know about Xiaolan’s ordinary days. Until the day Xiaolan gives up on writing letters to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Has Jinshi-sama heard anything about smallpox?” Even with Jinshi, Maomao had to be careful with her words.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hulang is looking into smallpox currently. You don’t know the infection source of smallpox, is that right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The court physicians have a tacit understanding that their conversations would contain things they couldn’t readily talk about. Jinshi, taking that into account as well, said the words &lt;em&gt;infection source&lt;/em&gt;. “I heard a man called Kokuyou is under suspicion. They say that he had spread smallpox by purposely infecting children with it,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So you know this much.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that guy the culprit?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao shook her head. “Although it is within his capabilities, he has no reason to do so.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then who could the culprit be?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“May I offer my speculation?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not speculation, but a deduction.” Jinshi’s face was like their inner palace days when he wanted to order her to solve the mystery.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao crossed her arms. &lt;em&gt;How rude&lt;/em&gt;, she thought. “They are going after children to inoculate them with smallpox. Their actions look the same as Kokuyou’s, but there is a point of difference.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is this difference?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Kokuyou does it when the children are healthy so the disease doesn’t aggravate. However, the culprit attacks unknown children. Also, being a random attacker, they would not be able to watch its development.” Maomao spoke like she was sorting out her mind. “&amp;#8230;It feels like a half-baked imitation.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What do you mean by imitation?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Imitating a doctor, perhaps? It feels like a child&amp;#8217;s game of make-believe where they only copy what they see and do not understand what they are doing.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A game of make-believe, huh? Then you mean, someone is doing the treatment to prevent smallpox, but they failed since they only learnt by imitation… “&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That is what I think, but I do not think there is such a person who knows about that smallpox treatment. Besides, it seems like most of the residents of the village that Kokuyou treated have died… Hm?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s wrong?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Come to think of it, I think I was told something like there was one adult survivor from that village.” Maomao slapped her brow. She had a feeling Yo told her this, but the memory was vague. “You might know if you ask the court lady by the name of Yo.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had a feeling Yo said something. She crunched on more pickles. It was perfectly salted, a flavour that made her want to eat it all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“However, what kind of person is this Kokuyou you talked about earlier?” Jinshi asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Oh?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Jinshi has never met him, huh?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought. She would meet all sorts of people day in and day out, so she nearly forgot who knew who. “He’s a man with half of his face covered in smallpox scars. He’s overly cheerful, but his medical knowledge is solid. Also, he’s quite stingy.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Medical knowledge, huh? It looks to me he’s not a court physician.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Correct. He’s a stray doctor. He’s moved around a lot, perhaps due to his misfortunate nature. Come to think of it, he’s asked a lot about horses and cows lately.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Horses and cows? Is this related to the medical treatment?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think it might be.” Maomao was also curious. “I am also curious, so when Kokuyou proposes something, may I come along as well?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll let them know.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Thank you very much.” Maomao bowed her head.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao and Jinshi had a bad habit of turning their conversations into work.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, it couldn’t be helped since they barely have any interests and hobbies in common.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Only that Jinshi enjoyed food from food stalls. It seems his tastes turn towards commoner fare.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao reached for the noodles. This too, was delicious, rich in flavour. “Come to think of it, Chue-san told me there is a good knife-cut noodles stand.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Knife-cut noodles, stand.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was something that Jinshi could never have. The imperial brother had no way of eating leisurely at a food stand in town. He would have to borrow clothes off a manservant and erase his body scent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, for a jaunt around town like they did before, the scar on his right cheek was too conspicuous, and concealing it as a burn scar would also stand out too much.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although everyone in the inner palace knew the eunuch Jinshi’s face, no one knew him in town back then.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Now that he was known in the capital as the imperial brother, there was no way he could casually dress up for a stroll around town.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Shall I ask if I can get takeaway?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The noodles will get soggy and cold. Most importantly, it tastes better when you slurp the hot noodles when you’re out in the cold.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You know very well how to eat it.” Maomao glanced at Suiren. There was no doubt this capable nanny practiced hard in knife-cutting noodles despite her old age. “Please summon for me when Suiren-sama cooks knife-cut noodles.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Got it, or rather, I’ll summon you over for other things too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As Maomao ate the last of the pickles, she thought, &lt;em&gt;I have to write a report.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On that, “&lt;em&gt;The imperial brother is in good health&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-20-a-new-casualty/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-19-health-check/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5269-67f157cfdb6e2' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250405#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5269&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5269-67f157cfdb6e2' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5269-67f157cfdb6e2' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-19-health-check/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
