    <item>
      <title>12.03 Endless Bothers</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-03-endless-bothers/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-03-endless-bothers/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 19 Sep 2023 08:23:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;12.03 Endless Bothers&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: There&amp;#8217;s something fun about jumping back and forth between arcs. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-02-factional-dispute/"&gt;Previous chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A few days after the old court physician’s unreasonable request, Maomao completed her work without much ado.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do something about it, your face.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As usual, there were a lot of injured. There would be four to five serious cases in a day, and among those would be injuries difficult to attribute as accidents from training. It was very apparent when you probe them for details on how the injuries came to be and they turn evasive.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had believed things would go back to normal with the return of the predator, but speaking of that predator….&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nooooo, I dun wanna go back to wooooork.”&lt;br&gt;“You can’t do that, Rakan-sama! We’re going back!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Pulling at the weirdo tactician who was clinging onto a pillar, was his aide Onsou.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao cheered for Onsou in her mind as she made a salve. Ointment and poultices were commonly prescribed, so they can’t let their supplies run out. However, it was not like she could stop assisting the court physicians with their surgeries, so she wasn’t about to make quite enough in advance.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When the old man clinging to the pillar like a cicada was gone, Court Physician Ri returned, covered in sweat. Beside him was the young military officer who got stabbed in the stomach by a wooden sword the other day.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Aren’t you off work today?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I am, so I was training in the drill hall,” Court Physician Ri answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You’re not a military officer, so what are you doing&lt;/em&gt;? wasn’t a question she could ask him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So, the one next to you?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He was at the drill hall so I brought him over. We told him to come everyday to monitor the condition of his stomach, but he hasn’t.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao and Court Physician Ri looked at the young military officer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve got the stitches so I’m already fine. No need to worry about it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You think so?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Ri grappled the young military officer from behind. Maomao tugged at his sash, and checked the bandages on his stomach.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“S-stinks!” Maomao cried out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What the hell!” Court Physician Ri exclaimed&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This is the smell of not changing the bandages, AND not taking any baths at all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s a young man for you! Strong body odour from crazy high metabolism! At least wipe yourself down with a damp cloth!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wh-what is this all of a sudden! The stitches will tear with that wrestling move!” The young military officer struggled, but Court Physician Ri proved much stronger with his excessive training.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao, have another court physician come over. We have to change his bandages right away.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood!” Maomao went to pull a court physician from the next room over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The bandages were wound tightly to staunch the bleeding, but when they removed them, it gave off a terrible stench.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s a little infected. Intense exercise? The stitches are broken.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did you make sure to take the antibiotic?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh please, your injury isn’t going to heal like this, and then you’ll be blaming us. Come now, shall we redo the stitching?” The court physician they called to help complained. He had a stubble and was in his thirties.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Unlike the inner palace, the court physicians of the imperial court were naturally outstanding. On top of that, as you would expect from seeing a great deal of patients at the medical office near the drill hall, they work while placing importance on efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The wound has been disinfected. I have the needle here.” Maomao prepared the tools and the two court physicians stitched up the injury.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The young military officer was made to bite on a bandage. His body was covered in bruises, unclear if it was from training or something else.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The re-stitching was in one location so it was finished in no time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The injury will never heal if you don’t change the bandages properly.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I also want you to take your medicine properly. That’s their purpose.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please return the underwear and pants we lent you the other day.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Perhaps wounded by Maomao’s words, the young military officer’s face turned bright red.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well then, I feel bad for mentioning it after redoing the stitching, but can you tell us who hurt you? You disappeared the moment we took our eyes off you, so it threw us right off.” Court Physician Ri hounded the military officer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It was an accident during training. Who my sparring partner was doesn’t matter.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah right, no matter how I see it, there was killing intent! You got stabbed in the belly by a broken sword, for goodness’ sake. You should thank your lucky stars that you got away with your organs unscathed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At Court Physician Ri’s words, Maomao and the court physician with the stubble also nodded.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“From your accent, you must be from Isei Province.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;” The young military officer fell silent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;For Court Physician Ri who had stayed at the western capital for around a year, it would be easy to identify their hometown by accent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So that means, your sparring opponent was a military officer from the imperial capital,” the court physician with the stubble confirmed as he stroked his chin.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Dang, if it’s a war by proxy, take that elsewhere, man. Aren’t you pissed that you keep getting attacked? Report that shit to the higher ups, hey.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even if I do report it, if it gets pigeonholed, it’d be for nothing,” the young military officer spat out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s worse for military officers when they’re weak. You should just get stronger.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao understood what he was saying, but for her, if they suffered a serious injury, it should be settled properly. It wasn’t just a problem for the military officers; it gave more work to the court physicians.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The young military officer was unexpectedly stubborn, so they had to tell him to change his bandages and eat his medicine properly at the very least. Not taking the effort would make the injury fester, which would be concerning.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Speaking of taking effort.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao recalled Jinshi, and thought that he hadn&amp;#8217;t called for her in a while.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;He’ll probably call for me when there’s something important going on.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While thinking so, she prepared the antibiotic drug to give to the military officer.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao didn’t love gossip, but nor did she hate it. She consolidated the rumours she got from hearing about the military officers’ troubles from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The power balance of the military was easy to understand:&amp;nbsp; the empress dowager faction was at the top, with the weirdo tactician’s next in the running.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao didn’t know the details. She didn’t think she needed to know, but there was a person who would carefully explain it all out to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Umm, so you see. Until now, the empress dowager’s faction was the dominant in the military, but these last couple of years, with Empress Gyokuyou’s emergence, the people from Isei Province have since banded together.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue was speaking glibly while Maomao was rebandaging. Partly because Maomao got transferred, Chue was now coming to the medical office where Maomao was. Because of Chue’s gender, the court physicians left it to Maomao to give her treatment. Perhaps to not let people see the skin of a married woman, they were alone, so it was really easy for them to chat up a storm.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That being said, the empress dowager faction wasn’t silent either. While Rakan-sama was around, the neutral faction functioned as the arbitrator, so nothing major happened. Hoooowever, with Rakan-sama’s period of absence, this equilibrium broke down. “&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahhh, so I seee.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao lifted up and felt Chue’s right arm. Her fingers could only twitch.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Rakan-sama’s faction is also having trouble. Terrifyingly, they also have people who have moved in from the empress dowager faction and the empress faction.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So that’s how it is.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao massaged Chue’s arm.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How interesting that you’re calling it the empress dowager or empress factions.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san is acquainted with both of them.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, I didn’t think either of them were the type to aggressively attack anyone, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The empress dowager was the one who abolished slavery and made a clinic in the inner palace for palace ladies who have nowhere to go. The empress, that is Empress Gyokuyou, wasn’t the type to stay silent when attacked, but that being said, she wasn’t a belligerent person.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“To say it correctly, the empress dowager faction is the faction that comprises her family as well as the current general-in-chief.” &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The general-in-chief?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. The current top brass of the military. Rakan-sama stands out more, but in reality, he’s next in rank. The general-in-chief was once the empress dowager’s guard. When she was pregnant with his imperial majesty, she got targeted by all sorts. At the time, the one who made a name for herself as the legendary attendant and wet nurse was Suiren-sama.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I feel like I’ve heard about this before, or not.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao has heard one or two anecdotes about Suiren, so she didn’t find it odd.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Empress Dowager-sama’s family was quite greedy. You can guess what happened when the young empress dowager was put into the inner palace, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Scary, scary.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao pressed the acupoints in Chue’s hand while wondering if acupuncture was effective. On the side, she recorded the degree of difference compared with Chue’s arm movement last time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And so, Empress Gyokuyou’s is Gyoku’en-sama’s faction?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well, that’s how it came to be, but I guess the people from the countryside banded together. The people being promoted are always those with connections in the imperial capital, so the country-bred and meritocratic Gyoku’en-sama became their rising star.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But Gyoku’en-sama is at an advanced age and there’s the issue with his successor, so aren’t they having a lot of trouble?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She felt she heard that even with his eldest son Gyoku’ou dead, his not returning to the western capital was due to the difficulties associated with his age.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, that’s why, aiming at that, they lifted their hand at the empress faction, and now we’re in this situation.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Haaah, I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s pointless even if the underlings fight about it.” Maomao thought it was absurd as she let go of Chue’s hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Uuugh, my old injury is hurtinggg.” Chue wanted to get a little more massage it seems. She rubbed her hand purposefully.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have other things to do, so that’s all for today.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Meanie.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao left the room. There was a tall court lady bearing a basket.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ummm, this would be…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was the new court lady with the short name. Perhaps due to her avoidance of showing skin, she was dressed quite formally. “Um, the herbal medicines you requested for have been delivered.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The basket contained herbal medicines. There was also Changsha, but newcomers were made to run errands for various posts.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Umm, please wait.” Maomao compared the ordered herbal medicine with the account book. “Rhubarb, spatterdock and cinnamon.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They were ingredients to make medicine to treat bruises.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s everything. No problem.” Maomao took the basket, and decided to put them into the medicine shelves as is. However, the new court lady didn’t make any move to leave.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, Maomao-san, she looks like she wants to say something to you.” Chue poked Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How can I help you?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I heard from Yao-san and the others, but do you work as a pharmacist in town?” The new court lady looked at Maomao with a serious expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I do.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, do you know people who work in the same trade? There’s a man who started out as a pharmacist within the last couple of years.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Started out as a pharmacist? Well, there is, I guess.” Maomao had one apprentice.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“T-there is?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, his name is Sazen. He works in a pharmacy in the pleasure district.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sazen… Pleasure district…. Could it be a fake name? He truly is a problematic person?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao closed her mouth. The situation was somewhat odd. Was it a mistake to talk to her about him untactfully?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That said, that guy did run away from the Shi clan revolt.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Being complicit in a revolt comes with a bunch of headaches. He wasn’t a bad guy, and most importantly, she had taken the effort to bring him up–looking for a pharmacist to succeed her was a pain.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please! Let me meet this Sazen person!” She gripped Maomao’s lapels and shook them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, but.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you won’t let us meet, I’ll find him myself! The pharmacy at the pleasure district, right?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I said something unnecessary.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Where the pharmacy at the pleasure district was concerned, there were not many of them. She’ll probably get to him in no time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, Maomao-san, how about you lead her there without a fuss?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Chue-san, Chue-san, it doesn’t concern you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Fufufu, Chue-san will be coming along too.” Chue smiled happily.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As the new court lady gripped onto her lapels, Maomao sighed, at a loss at what to do.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: Something I noticed while translating this chapter. It assumes Maomao has met the Empress Dowager Anshi, when in the webnovel I don&amp;#8217;t think she ever did.  Also the empress dowager character that is said to have abolished slavery and created the inner palace clinic was, in earlier chapters, established to be the former empress dowager who was also known as the empress regnant. Did the characters get merged or did the current one take the previous one&amp;#8217;s achievements as her own?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;The grappling move that Court Physician Ri executed on the military officer is specifically the full nelson. It sounded awkward to translate that as is so I just wrote around it. &amp;#8220;Court Physician Ri pulled the full nelson on the military officer &amp;#8230; the stitches will tear with the full nelson&amp;#8221; doesn&amp;#8217;t sound quite as nice, also what does that even mean???&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;The general-in-chief =大将軍&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;Medicinal stuff encountered this chapter: &lt;ruby&gt;大黄&lt;rp&gt;(ダイオウ&lt;/rp&gt;&lt;/ruby&gt; &lt;em&gt;rheum officinale&lt;/em&gt;, 川骨 &lt;em&gt;nuphar japonica&lt;/em&gt;, 桂皮 &lt;em&gt;cinnamomum verum&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-04-the-person-yo-seeks/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-03-endless-bothers/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-3954-67f157d009c4d' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250405#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=3954&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-3954-67f157d009c4d' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-3954-67f157d009c4d' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-03-endless-bothers/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
