    <item>
      <title>SS: The Villa (2)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-the-villa-2/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-the-villa-2/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2024 23:10:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;SS: The Villa&amp;nbsp;(2)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-the-villa-1/"&gt;Previous chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was on her third full cup of tea since she started chatting with Ah Duo when there was a commotion. An attendant came over and once again whispered something into Ah Duo’s ear.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Following that, Ah Duo’s facial expression blatantly changed. She then excused herself and went off somewhere, leaving Maomao alone at the table.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(What on earth happened?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;More importantly, what should I do? &lt;/em&gt;Maomao thought as she drank her fourth cup of tea an attendant poured for her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was when Maomao returned from her trip to the toilet that she became aware of what happened. As expected, the urge came after drinking nothing but tea, so she got an attendant to guide her there.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After witnessing a doctor rush into a room, Maomao found herself peeking in too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The attendant who was guiding her panicked, but it couldn’t be helped since curiosity won. She saw Maomao as a girl of good breeding, but even if her appearance had been cleaned up, she was someone brought up in the pleasure district after all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was a boy with a ghastly complexion slumped over inside the room. Ah Duo gripped the child’s hands, and the doctor was examining him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The other child standing around them was on the verge of tears. They were holding onto a cup. There was a dark brown residue on the rim.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(What’s that?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao realised why the boy was slumped over. The doctor seems to have already realised what happened, as he laid the child into a sleeping position and draped blankets over him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao knew the treatment too, so she prepared water for the child to drink, taking over for the maids surrounding them who had no idea what to do.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although she had entered the room in the confusion of the moment, she started to assist the doctor, saying, “Well, don’t worry about it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was after when the child’s condition stabilised, that she, for some reason, found a kindred spirit in the doctor. It seems Maomao had good chemistry with the elderly doctor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I couldn’t do anything.” Ah Duo sat down haggardly on a chair. Maomao found the former consort’s expression to be something complicated.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Is she thinking about the son she lost?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Whether he was lost or gone, Maomao didn’t care. It was just that Ah Duo looked awfully exhausted.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m sorry. I showed something unsightly to a guest.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, it’s fine. Don’t worry about it.” Rather, Maomao was more familiar with this sort of thing than keeping up her appearance for a prospective marriage partner.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao picked up the cup the child was holding. She sniffed it and found it smelling faintly of alcohol.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is it grape wine? It’s brewed a bit stronger, though,” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo nodded. “Yeah, that’s right. You know well. It suits the tastes of the original owner of this palace.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had said it in a roundabout way, but she probably meant that the emperor also came around to this villa. This place, being neither the imperial court nor the inner palace, might be a place where he could feel at ease. It was a little complicated considering Empress Gyokuyou, who was now the empress, though.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It appears the management was sloppy. I can’t believe the children had ended up drinking it for fun.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We cannot have this&lt;/em&gt;, Ah Duo sighed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao tilted her head as she looked at the sleeping child. The boy wasn’t ten years old yet, but he gave off an odd feeling.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;His chubby face was now pale.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I thought the child had quite a big appetite but I didn’t think he would go as far as to raid the storehouse,” Ah Duo said as she brushed hair away from the child’s face with her fingers, exuding a maternal feel that differed from her appearance of a young man.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is this child an orphan too?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. He barely escaped with his life during the time he was being treated as a slave of the foreign tribes. He must have suffered a lot. His obsession with food is abnormal.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Abnormal appetite, huh.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When the foreign tribes have a lot of slaves&amp;#8211;that is, male slaves&amp;#8211;they deal with it in a certain way. These slaves would originally be dealt with by forcing them to be male livestock. They could be made to become the officials that even the inner palace had.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The boy was not yet ten, but looking at his appetite and his plump figure, he was probably given that treatment,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Has this happened before?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. The previous time, it was fruit juice. It seems he cannot forget the things he ate and drank in his hometown a long time ago. Once he finds something close to it, he puts it in his mouth with no regard for the consequences.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But it seems in most cases, things that look similar taste different, so he gets sad from it. His sense of nostalgia must be spurring his appetite too.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If only I was talented in cooking, then I could reproduce the flavours of his hometown.” Ah Duo smiled sadly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao tilted her head and narrowed her eyes. “Was this child’s hometown close to the national border?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. Bandits seemed to have attacked that area a few years ago.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Was he a child of a merchant?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, just a farmer’s child, it seems. What about it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The points that didn’t make sense to Maomao started to come together.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The national border was inland and had low temperatures, which limited the kinds of crops that could be grown there.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Wine aside, grape juice wasn’t something that commoners can consume.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They could eat a crop that was grown inland or could be preserved, though.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao tried to think of a crop that was just like that.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(If I remember correctly, for fruits, something like citrus would be on the market.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While she thought that, she hit upon an idea.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can you lend me your kitchen? Also, I’d require some other ingredients too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wh-what is this, all of a sudden?” Ah Duo was taken aback by the sudden request.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wrote down a list of ingredients on a wooden slip and passed it to an attendant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you trying to make what that child wants to drink?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao, looking a little bit like she was having fun, headed to the kitchen, guided by an attendant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;To prepare a certain thing, Maomao had faced a large pot for one dual hour. She poured bright grape-coloured water into a glass cup, set it on a tray and carried it over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When she returned to the room after finishing her task, the chubby child was awake. Ah Duo looked at the child anxiously,&amp;nbsp; concerned about the sudden increase in people.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Why?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And over there, sat a man with a scar running across his otherwise too-beautiful face. Standing beside him was Gaoshun with his usual exhausted look.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi stared at Maomao with an inexplicable expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(He’s always staring at me.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It happened to be a pain for Maomao that she wanted to tell him off for his rude and strange habit, but being who he is, she couldn’t. Despite how she was, Maomao still paid attention to propriety in her own way.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao bowed and set the tray before Ah Duo.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s still warm though.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She stuck a straw into the cup to make it easier to drink from.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo gently brought the straw to the child’s mouth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The child looked doubtful, but after taking a sip, his eyes lit up. He removed the straw and gulped down the rest of the glass.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;tastes like what mum made for me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo couldn’t hide her surprise when she saw the teary child.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What in the world is this?” Waving the emptied glass, she asked Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao took the glass off her,&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please wait a moment.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And left the room to get a certain something from the kitchen.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo wasn’t the only one who tilted her head at what Maomao brought over. Jinshi and Gaoshun did too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;What she poured into a glass cup was a dark liquid, a colour significantly different to the drink from before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao squeezed in the juice of a halved citrus and stirred it with a straw.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The darkish colour, once mixed with the citrus, transformed into a vibrant purplish red.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo, the child, and the attendants widened their eyes in shock.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi and Gaoshun watched in amazement.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Like always, you know peculiar things,” Jinshi muttered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t that she was using sage arts. Maomao just knew about it. That if you add citrus juice into the dark liquid it will change colour.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And speaking of the identity of this dark liquid.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. It becomes like this when you add this juice into black soybean broth,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Black soybean… you say?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, black soybean.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She handed the glass cup to Ah Duo, who still had a look of disbelief. Ah Duo took a sip,&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It certainly seems to be black soybean,” she murmured.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had strained it through a cloth to improve its taste and added a fruity flavour by incorporating citrus&amp;#8211;which also changed the colours to a vivid hue. It wasn’t unreasonable for the young child to mistake it with fruit juice in his memory, all the more since it had been sweetened with flavouring.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Black soybean keeps well, so it would probably be widespread in inland villages too. Same goes for citrus.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The villagers would probably drink the soybean broth to not waste it. Although it included a little ingenuity, this was the true form of the fruit juice-like thing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While Maomao explained, the child tried to take the broth from Ah Duo. Ah Duo passed it over without getting angry, but Maomao took it away from the child.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The child reached out, tried to take it back from Maomao, but she gave him water instead.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Isn’t it fine to give him this much?” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I personally don’t mind, but it’s not good for this child,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What do you mean?” Ah Duo regarded Maomao doubtfully.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao cast her eyes down and carefully selected her words. “&amp;#8230;may I be direct?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Go ahead,” Ah Duo told her, so Maomao decided to say something that was a little difficult to say.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao placed the broth out of the child’s reach and explained why she confiscated it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“From what I see with this child’s weight, Ah Duo-sama dotes on him, but I think it’s not the same as spoiling. Just now, I had him drink something sweet as a special occasion, but I don’t think I really should have given that to him.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What do you mean?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao decided to explain this child’s condition. The doctor seemed to have realised, but couldn’t say it properly since he was dealing with Ah Duo.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This child always overeats. Does he drink a lot of water and wet his bed?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;now that you mention it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You shouldn’t just give him what he likes to eat. With the way things are going, this child’s limbs go numb, his eyesight will worsen, and before long, he will come up with other illnesses and his extremities will rot.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a disease prone to affect those who overindulge in eating. This was the first time she had seen a child get it, but it was probably the same thing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even though he wants it, I can’t give it to him?” Ah Duo asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Was that how Ah Duo-sama was raised?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo widened her eyes. &lt;em&gt;Now that you mention it,&lt;/em&gt; she looked at the child.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although Ah Duo did give birth to a child, she has never raised one, so she probably has not experienced the act of scolding before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo looked at the child with a complicated expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Due to his pitiful circumstances, she might have spoiled him specially. Not that it was a bad thing; in reality, the child was looking at Ah Duo like he depended on her. He had been reduced to a slave, but seeing that expression made her wonder how much effort did it take to make it possible for him to look at an adult like that.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ah Duo shook her head at the child who was acting spoilt and gave him water instead. She saw the child make a sad face and pet his head.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Bear with it. It’s for your own good,” she admonished him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao started to clear away the glass cup, but the attendants took over. The maids, who had been silent until now about what Maomao was doing, having no idea what they should do, finally found something they could do, and cleaned up efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Upon closer look, they were the attendants who served Ah Duo’s palace in the inner palace. They probably went to Ah Duo after their contract ended.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Since Maomao had nothing to do, she decided to leave the room and return to the gazebo.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;For some reason, Jinshi accompanied her to the gazebo. He had a cloth bag in his hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No matter where you go, you have to stick your nose into things, huh.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No such thing,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(You’re the one who stuck his nose into everything the time we were in the inner palace.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She sat down and watched the lake absentmindedly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi unravelled the cloth bag, and took out a large flower kanzashi. It bore a peony flower arranged from silk dyed in light red.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He picked it up and slipped it over Maomao’s right ear.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My apology for making you wait.” A gentle smile appeared on Jinshi’s face. Even with the scar running across his cheek, his alluring face remained the same.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Come to think of it.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This was the moment she recalled why she came to this place.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Gaoshun ran over to them in a fluster. “Bad news!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;‘What is it?” Jinshi said to his hardworking retainer with a look of displeasure, a complete change from just now.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Rakan-sama&amp;#8230;is currently heading over here. For some reason, he has his heir, Rahan-dono, wrapped up in a bamboo mat, dragged by a horse.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;““&amp;#8230;””&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao and Jinshi exchanged glances.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Excuse me, Jinshi-sama. This is it for me.” Maomao hitched up her long dress and dashed off at full speed. On her face, was an expression like she was looking at every possible filth in the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“H-hey!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard Jinshi’s voice from behind her, but it was of no concern to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Her first priority was to run away until the strange voice behind her disappeared.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(With this, the marriage meeting has been ruined.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While Maomao thought that, on her ear, the bright peony flower petals shook in the wind.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-the-villa-2/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4602-67f157d04c1f7' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250405#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4602&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4602-67f157d04c1f7' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4602-67f157d04c1f7' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-the-villa-2/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
