    <item>
      <title>14.17 Changsha, Peerless</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-17-changsha-peerless/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-17-changsha-peerless/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 04 Jan 2025 07:07:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.17 Changsha, Peerless&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-16-girls-night-out/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The day after the court physician assistants’ dinner party, Maomao felt a heavy weight on her stomach.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue was asleep on Maomao’s stomach, and in the corner of her room, Yo was rolled up in the bedding.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Umm.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They hadn’t been drinking, but the vibe was as if they had. Picking a restaurant close to the dorms had been the correct answer, just as Chue had planned. The establishment ran quite late, so when they left the store, it was at a time where they couldn’t arrange for carriages either.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yao and En’en should be sleeping in Changsha’s room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They talked about all sorts of things afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And speaking of how it turned out…&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Good grief, even though the two of you understand in your minds, aren’t you letting your emotions dictate too much?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was Changsha who bluntly said what everyone else had been dying to say regarding Yao and En’en up until now.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Normally, Yao would be a little more defiant, but she was currently reflecting on her own actions, so she quietly took it all in. En’en was raring to argue back, but Yao stopped her, so Changsha’s incessant chatter continued to gain the upper hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Setting aside how she’s talking to her seniors…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Changsha was the youngest among them. This little girl continued to spit out sound arguments.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So I was thinking, but aren’t we in this stalemate because you’ve been treating Yao-san like a child and enabling everything? It may be Maomao-san’s home&amp;#8212;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not my home.” Maomao denied it as always.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, drop that for now. You’d have to be finding it odd that they have been freeloading for so long. At any rate, this is the house of a bachelor close to your age. Yes, I know that the estate is large, but it’s not like you can stay there for years, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You are correct. I understand,” En’en agreed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Despite that, Changsha’s expression darkened. “But you’re somehow spoiling her, En’en-san. That’s why Yao-san continues to not make sound judgements even though she actually finds it strange. Yao-san has more common sense than her appearance suggests, so she would had to have stopped because she has En’en-san looking out for her. Yes, you had to have been indirectly indicating to her through actions to leave the place, but you never said it out loud. It’s because you never told her it&amp;#8217;s bad to continue to stay there as she&amp;#8217;s interested in him. Rahan-sama, was it?”&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What should I compare this vibe to?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was the vibe of leaving side dishes out in the corner of the kitchen during summer and forgetting it for a few days. How it clumps together in that characteristic way when you lift the lid of the pot.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yao’s lips trembled. Her face reddened.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en had a demonic expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue continued to eat rice. Yo’s eyes were shining just a little from the girls’ talk.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao requested for a drink refill for the time being.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-sama! Deserves! A! More! Proper! Man!” En’en said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My grandaunt remained unmarried for her entire life because her father said exactly what En’en-san said and didn’t allow men to approach his daughter. On her deathbed, the last words she left behind were that if her father was in paradise, let him be dragged down to hell. Are you fine with having Yao-san resent you like that?” Changsha asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Th-that is…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-san, I believe you have already realised, but how about changing your approach to get close to Rahan-sama? Yes, yes, I know. You are still unsure whether your feelings towards Rahan-sama are that of love or curiosity. But how about we set that aside for now? At this rate, let alone making him uncomfortable, it’ll worsen your impressions. It’ll influence you at work too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“At work too?” Yao reacted to the word ‘work.’&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good one, Changsha.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;For better or worse, Changsha had been raised in a normal household, so she had finesse in this topic. She could speak of the parts that Maomao would avoid getting into because she had been raised in an environment where she could look at any problem optimistically.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She would be getting into a difficult scene through her association with the court physicians from now on, but right now, her attitude was working for the better.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-san, how do you want Rahan-sama to see you?” Changsha asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Good question,” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you want to be fussed over as a beauty?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No way. That’s a pain.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A pain, huh?” Chue whispered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought the same. Yao was good-looking and she had a generous figure as well. That is to say, this was the trouble of someone who has it all. A topic that Maomao and Chue had no relation to.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Jinshi would be the one with that prime trouble, isn’t that right?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao took a sip of the tea a staff brought to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, do you want him to recognise you as a competent person?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Y-yes.” Yao gave an ambiguous affirmation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en eyed Changsha sullenly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, how about you go home for once?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How did you get to that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you want to be seen as a competent person, don’t you need to have control over your family, not just at work?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“She’s not wrong,” Chue said as she ate up the last of the stewed pork. “Yao-san’s uncle is still in the western capital, riiight?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, now would be the perfect opportunity. It’d be good if you can take control of your family while your uncle is awaaay.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;She said something disturbing…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue quickly cleaned up the leftovers. “While your uncle is away, who is managing your family?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My mum.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, is Yao-san’s mother good at this kind of work?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I don’t think she’s very good at it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, you should just take over for her. Or do you have your hands full with your current job as a court physician assistant, so you can’t do anythiiing?” Chue goaded her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had thoughts about this. Yao would only burn herself out by working too hard and cramming too much into her workload. It was exactly the same as Yo who wanted to return to the smallpox infection site.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, Chue was purposely pushing Yao into doing it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao kept silent, thinking the other woman must have something up her sleeve.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo looked like she wanted to say something, but Maomao quietly stopped her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Going home sounds like a good idea. After all, I don’t think you’d be able to live alone properly assuming you do leave Rahan-sama’s place. If that’s the case, it’ll be better for you to be at home while you do the work at home,” Changsha said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please wait, Changsha-san,” En’en said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is it, En’en-san?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did you just say, live alone?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I did.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en’s face twisted.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I mean, if she wants to become a competent person, it’ll be weird to have En’en-san take care of her meals and laundry. If so, she needs to be able to live alone, but I wonder if Yao-san isn’t that skilled with housework. Even if she could wash the bandages, she probably couldn’t iron clothes. If so, it’ll be better for her give up on that and go home.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even if she goes home, someone aside from me will do it. If so, it’s fine for me to do it, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There’s a big difference. It’s like this, En’en-san and Yao-san, you two do the same work at the same workplace, right? But once you go home, Yao-san does nothing and En’en-san does everything for her. No matter how capable at work Yao-san is, doesn’t that mean En’en-san will overwhelmingly be superior?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en got fatally struck by invisible arrows. Maomao thought that Changsha was truly scary.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“After all, if she can’t win against En’en-san when it comes to housework, then wouldn’t she still be seen as a competent person if she were to go home and take over her family on behalf of her uncle instead?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“B-but…” En’en looked at Yao pleadingly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re right. I’ve been spoiled. Housework is still work. I thought I could do everything when I couldn’t.” Yao was very meek.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And Changsha gave the meek Yao even less leeway. “Then, you’ll be going home.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. Do I have anything else that is lacking?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You do,” Changsha said profoundly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can you tell me in detail?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. I will need to hear in detail on what your feelings towards Rahan-sama are.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo’s eyes shone again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What you like about him, what about him that interests you? Please tell me without leaving anything out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en, who was on the verge of death, pleaded for her to stop.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Changsha, scaryyy.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let’s never be cornered by Changsha. Just Changsha&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211;This was how the rooms were allocated.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yao and En’en were in Changsha’s room to continue the girls’ talk from hell.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-18-random-attacker/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-17-changsha-peerless/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5234-67f157d057089' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250405#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5234&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5234-67f157d057089' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5234-67f157d057089' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-17-changsha-peerless/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
